==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Peculiarity
<hw>Pe*cul`iar"i*ty</hw>
<pr>(p⟦esl⟧*k⟦umac⟧l`y⟦acr⟧r"⟦icr⟧*t⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Peculiarities</plw>
<pr>(p⟦esl⟧*k⟦umac⟧l`y⟦acr⟧r"⟦icr⟧*t⟦icr⟧z)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The quality or state of being peculiar; individuality;
singularity.</def> <rj><au>Swift.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is peculiar; a special and distinctive
characteristic or habit; particularity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The smallest <qex>peculiarity</qex> of temper or manner.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Exclusive possession or right.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bp. Hall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peculiarize</ent>⟦br⟧
